15/03/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The international community expects Macedonia's NGO sector to work actively in the elections process. This was the conclusion of a meeting Tuesday (14 March) among President Branko Crvenkovski, EU and OSCE envoys Erwan Fouere and Carlos Pais and US Ambassador to Skopje Gillian Milovanovic. They met as part of Crvenkovski's initiative for a public debate on preparations for the vote later this year. He plans to meet soon with representatives of the political parties and religious organisations. (Macedonian Government Web site - 15/03/06; A1 TV, Telma TV - 14/03/06)
